    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - PISTON
        RINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PISTON RINGS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Faulty rings cannot always be detected by visual inspection. Therefore, whenever a piston is
                        removed from a cylinder, it is recommended that the piston rings be replaced.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect
                    <emph type="bold">NEW</emph>
                    rings for cleanliness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to installing the rings on the piston, check each ring for proper gap as
                    follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Push the ring down into the cylinder bore making sure the ring is square with the
                        cylinder wall.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Measure the gap between the ends of each ring with a feeler gauge as shown in
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e105_113.xml" xrefid="ef1050615">6.15</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        . Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">"SPECIFICATIONS"</emph>
                        for ring gap. Discard any used ring which does not meet the specifications.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
